### OPA + Zanzibar authorization examples against the demo model.
### Requires: docker compose up (bootstrap.sh)
### Select the "dev" environment to use the variables below.
###
### READ MODE — tokenless `input.subject` requests below only work when OPA
### runs with REQUIRE_TOKEN_FOR_READS=false (the base/test stack: env.sh
### exports it). The keycloak/playground overlay pins the SECURE token-only
### mode (REQUIRE_TOKEN_FOR_READS=true), where tokenless subject reads are
### rejected (`allow` → false). On that stack either:
###   * use the `input.token` variants (mint one: keycloak/get-token.sh, or
###     grant_type=password against the pgauthz realm), or
###   * recreate opa tokenless for cookbook use:
###     REQUIRE_TOKEN_FOR_READS=false docker compose -f compose.yml \
###       -f compose-authzen.yml -f compose-keycloak.yml -f compose-playground.yml \
###       up -d --no-deps opa

### =====================================================================
### ACCESS CHECKS (allow)
### =====================================================================

### Alice can read payroll doc (via payroll_team membership)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

### Alice can read payroll doc (via payroll_team membership) with subject from token
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "token": "{{access_token_alice}}",
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Alice can edit payroll doc (payroll_clerk → can_edit)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "action":   "can_edit",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Alice cannot read tax doc (wrong team)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_tax_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": false }

###

### Bob (advisor on engagement) can read payroll doc
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Carol (client org member) can read client-space doc
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "carol" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Carol cannot edit client-space doc (clients get read-only)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "carol" },
    "action":   "can_edit",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": false }

###

### Carol can read a private doc via viewer
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "carol" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_private_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Dave cannot read the private doc (no explicit grant)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "dave" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_private_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": false }

###

### Eva (accounting_team) can read accounting doc
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_acc_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### Eva cannot read payroll doc (wrong team)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": false }

###

### =====================================================================
### ACCESS CHECK WITH CONTEXT (conditional tuples / ABAC)
### =====================================================================

### Access check with context — useful for time-based or IP-based conditions.
### Context values are forwarded to the PostgreSQL condition engine.
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    "context":  { "current_time": "2026-03-12T10:00:00Z" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### =====================================================================
### ACCESS CHECK WITH CONTEXTUAL TUPLES
### =====================================================================

### Frank normally cannot read doc_client_001.
### With a contextual tuple granting viewer, access is granted
### for this request only — the tuple is never persisted.
POST {{base_url}}/authz/allow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "frank" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_001" },
    "contextual_tuples": [
      {
        "user_type":    "internal_user",
        "user_id":      "frank",
        "user_relation": null,
        "relation":     "viewer",
        "object_type":  "document",
        "object_id":    "doc_client_001"
      }
    ]
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": true }

###

### =====================================================================
### BATCH ACCESS CHECK (evaluations)
### =====================================================================

### Batch: check multiple permissions for Alice on payroll doc (execute_all).
POST {{base_url}}/authz/evaluations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "evaluations": [
      { "action": "can_read",   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_edit",   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_delete", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } }
    ]
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": [true, true, false] }

###

### Batch: different users/resources in one call (each evaluation has its own subject).
POST {{base_url}}/authz/evaluations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "evaluations": [
      { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" }, "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },   "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },   "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } }
    ]
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": [true, true, false] }

###

### Batch: deny_on_first_deny — stops at first false, remaining are null.
POST {{base_url}}/authz/evaluations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "semantic": "deny_on_first_deny",
    "evaluations": [
      { "action": "can_read",   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_edit",   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_delete", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_read",   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_acc_001" } }
    ]
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": [true, true, false, null] }

###

### Batch: permit_on_first_permit — stops at first true.
POST {{base_url}}/authz/evaluations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },
    "semantic": "permit_on_first_permit",
    "evaluations": [
      { "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
      { "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_acc_001" } },
      { "action": "can_read", "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_tax_001" } }
    ]
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": [false, true, null] }

###

### =====================================================================
### RESOURCE SEARCH (accessible_objects)
### =====================================================================

### Which documents can Bob read?
POST {{base_url}}/authz/accessible_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["doc_acc_001", "doc_folder_payroll_q1_001", "doc_folder_tax_001", "doc_payroll_001", "doc_tax_001"] }
### (3 engagement docs as advisor + 2 docs in the workpapers folder bob owns)

###

### Which documents can Carol read?
POST {{base_url}}/authz/accessible_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "carol" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["doc_client_001", "doc_client_002", "doc_client_private_001"] }

###

### =====================================================================
### RESOURCE SEARCH WITH PAGINATION (accessible_objects_page)
### =====================================================================

### Bob's readable documents — first page (limit=2, offset=0)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/accessible_objects_page
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document" },
    "page":     { "limit": 2, "offset": 0 }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["doc_acc_001", "doc_folder_payroll_q1_001"] }

###

### Bob's readable documents — second page (limit=2, offset=2)
POST {{base_url}}/authz/accessible_objects_page
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
    "action":   "can_read",
    "resource": { "type": "document" },
    "page":     { "limit": 2, "offset": 2 }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["doc_folder_tax_001", "doc_payroll_001"] }

###

### =====================================================================
### ACTION SEARCH (permitted_actions)
### =====================================================================

### What can Alice do on the payroll doc?
POST {{base_url}}/authz/permitted_actions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["can_read", "can_edit"] }

###

### What can Carol do on a client-space doc?
POST {{base_url}}/authz/permitted_actions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "input": {
    "subject":  { "type": "client_user", "id": "carol" },
    "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_001" }
  }
}
### Expected: { "result": ["can_read"] }
